  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Place your hand flat onto the&nbsp;<strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces of&nbsp;chicken</p>\r\n<p>Lay a sheet of cling film or greaseproof paper over the<strong>&nbsp;chicken breast</strong><strong>&nbsp;halves&nbsp;</strong>and bash the <strong>chicken</strong> with a rolling pin to an even thickness throughout&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut in half</p>\r\n<p>Combine half of the <strong>Greek-style yoghurt</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> and the juice of 1/2&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>lemon </strong>in a large bowl with a large drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chicken</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) and roll each flattened piece up tightly to form a cigar shape&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the chicken is cooked through - this is your <strong>chicken gyros&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into <strong>chips</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add them to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the baking tray in the oven and cook for 20-25 min or until they're golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>cucumber</strong> in half, scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon and throw the watery seeds away - grate the remaining&nbsp;<strong>cucumber</strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the remaining <strong>lemon</strong> into&nbsp;wedges</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the remaining <strong>Greek-style yoghurt</strong> with the <strong>grated cucumber</strong> and<strong>&nbsp;chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) and the juice of 1<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[2]</span> <strong>lemon wedge<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> - this is your<strong> tzatziki&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1041.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
